[normal]Decline of Nations[bold] [bold]a)[bold]&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; 
[normal]Moral Decline or Degeneration[bold]&#xa0;
[normal]The condition of moral decline is seen as 
[normal]preceding
[normal] w
[normal]ith the decline in quality of
[normal] life, as well as the decline of nations (Conservapedia.com)
[normal]&#xa0;
[normal]An established morality is as 
[normal]necessary as good government to the welfare of society.  Societies disintegrate from within more frequently than they are broken up by extern
[normal]al pressures (Judge Devlin, Law
[normal]yer and Jurist 1905 – 1992)
[normal]&#xa0;
