[normal]b)[bold]&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; 
[normal]Rome[bold]Over 5 centuries the ancient Roman Empire spr
[normal]ead to include an area from the 
[normal]Atlantic to the 
[normal]Euphr
[normal]ates, and England to the Sahara, 
[normal]until it succumbed to the Four Danger Zones of Morality (Smith 286)
[normal]Wealth, Force, Sex and Speech
[normal]  (
[normal]Affluence – Rich
[normal]es
[normal] –
[normal] Greed)
[normal]The needs of online safety can be mirrored in the decline of
[normal] moral standards through the 
[normal]media, which in Roman times was the violence of the Gladiatorial combat which was essentially murder.  Rome couldn’t eventually fill its military ranks and the decadent civilians could not mount any sort of 
[normal]effective defence.  The Theodosian Code
[normal] eventual
[normal]ly displayed an emotional confusion between sin and crime that would have been alien to the classical Roman law (159).  When a nation 
[normal]possesses
[normal] everything it needs and more, it become
[normal]s
[normal] myopic, short sighted and no longer plans ahead to prolong the life of 
[normal]the nation
[normal].  We cannot afford to be a showcase of smugness and apathy.
[normal]In 1993 the average American child had watched 8,000 televised murders and 10,000 acts of violence before finishing elementary school (
[normal]American Psychological Association)
[normal](Novelguide
[normal])
